name: Direct Hit/Tit Patrol Split 7"
description:
The split between the two bands will be released through Delaware label Madison Underground Recordings. The record will be pressed on glow-in-the-dark vinyl, and will feature tri-color screen-printed covers from Josh Davis, a.k.a. Dead Meat, based out of Chicago, Ill. 

Direct Hit contributes two new songs about mutants, telepathy, and science gone wrong to the release, while Tit Patrol offers three harmony and theremin-drenched tunes about ghosts, supernatural illness, and hallucination. Free music from Direct Hit is available at directhit.bandcamp.com; Tit Patrol’s entire catalog is available for free at titpatrol.bandcamp.com.

1. Ghost Flu
2. Slimming Figure 
3. Delusions of Adequacy
